    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to drawings or works in other media that are scaled representation of physical objects, meaning they represent the object and its parts in precisely the same proportion as the original, although it may be larger or smaller than the original.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>按實物比例所繪製的圖樣或作品，其所呈現的物件與部件和原件的比例相同，但比原件來得大或小。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zeichnung oder Arbeit in einem anderen Medium, die eine maßstabsgetreue Darstellung eines physischen Objekts ist; das heißt, das Objekt und seine Teile werden in genau derselben Proportion wie im Original dargestellt, auch wenn die Darstellung größer oder kleiner als das Original sein kann.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refere-se aos desenhos ou trabalhos em outros meios que são representações em escala de objetos físicos. Eles representam o objeto e suas partes na mesma proporção do original, embora possam ser maiores ou menores do que o original.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000179/VP-intern</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
